article.headline: Stony Brook 81, UMBC 69
article.story: EDs: APNewsNow. Stony Brook 81, UMBC 69. STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Brian Dougher scored 23 points and Stony Brook defeated Maryland-Baltimore County 81-69 on Monday night. The Seawolves (12-7, 4-2 America East Conference) outrebounded the Terriers (1-17, 0-5) 50-24 with Dallis Joyner grabbing 12 and Tommy Brenton 11 for Stony Brook. The Seawolves scored 40 points in the paint and 15 second-chance points. UMBC was 2-for-7 from the field and had four turnovers early as Stony Brook took a 22-7 lead on Brenton's free throws with 11:56 left in the first half. The Retrievers pulled within 50-45 with 15:57 remaining on Adrian Satchell's layup, but Stony Brook scored seven straight to pull away. Dougher's layup gave the Seawolves a 57-45 lead with 13:10 remaining. Muhammad El-Amin added 20 points, Brenton 14 and Chris Martin 12 for Stony Brook. Chauncey Gilliam had 24 points for the Retrievers and Shawn Grant added 11.
